I've been going to his other grocery store for years, because they make it very easy to send money internationally.  They are also conveniently located to me right off 12th Street. I came back from Mexico and was saddened to learn that his grocery store had burned down.  I remember the Owner had told me about the new restaurant that he opened up called Benito's Place. I wanted to ask him for his recommendation for a new store that transfers money internationally. Come to find out, he told me he now offers the money transfer service right in his restaurant.  That was more than great luck for me, since he already had my information and the recipient's already in his system. Since I had been craving something Mexican ever since I returned, I wanted to try out his quesadillas. They were mad good

Some friends had the pleasure of inviting me to Benitos Place it is good to feel the flaor of your country normally i have visited other restaurants from my country but i never  found  that flavor that reminds me of my house, very good I hope you keep the consistency and originality thanks guys !

I am so excited to see Benitos join the neighborhood! Food here is great and the place has an intimate, neighborhood feel.  The first time I stopped by right after it opened, I ordered some tacos to go. When I mentioned to the man who was taking my order that I was excited to see them open, he said "Do you have a couple extra minutes? I'd like you to try this new dish were making." Hard to say no to an offer like that! It ended up being some sauce and cabbage on a bed of plantain chips. It was absolutely delicious, and I was told it's usually served with fish or chicken.  Anyway, would highly recommend, especially if you're looking for some down-to-earth food!

Great new place with decent prices. Has a lot of potential and so far are heading in the right direction. Staff here is very polite and professional, the place is a little small but doable, and most important the food is on point! The Mexican Tortadas are amazing! The Baleadas are made perfectly! I'm Salvadorean, so I rate the pupusas everywhere I go, and the Pupusas here are Great! Hot and fresh and tasty! I recommend this place to anyone looking for a quick bite to eat or just come in to enjoy the experience and come with your family.

Tonight was my first time trying Honduran food. Yum.  I had the pastelitos de carne o polio. Delicious.  My dining companion had a fabulous fried chicken with plantains dish. They also had old standbys (read: Americanized tastes) like nachos and fajitas.  The owner and his staff are very friendly and glad to have new customers. He mentioned he'd be expanding his menu soon and getting a liquor license.  Brightly lit and many tvs playing. Not my thing.  The prices are btw $10-$15 for entrees.  Overall, i'd say it's a great addition to the neighborhood.
